Recommender System EDA practical Assignment:¶

Task To do¶

Perform an Exploratory Data Analyst using the datasets in order to have a better understanding on the different dataset:

We are in this project performing an EDA on movies dataset focus on user ratings , movie ids and movie titles because they could be use for the creation of the recommender system.

So as orientation goal we will try to make :

  • Analysis by user ratings, movie ids and movie titles:
    • What is the distribution of ratings, movie ids and titles
    • What item has relationship with high user ratings : userId? movie Id? movie titles? popularity? budget? etc.
      • What are the top movies sorted on the basis of user ratings on a particular movie ?
      • Which item explained the previous question: budget? popularity? movie titles? etc.
      • How likely the user rating will be for a movie ?
  • and more if needed.

That is why we need distribution of rating, movieId and movie titles and more

The movies dataset -> https://www.kaggle.com/rounakbanik/the-movies-dataset

original_language, status¶

In [16]:
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
sns.catplot(x="original_language", y="rating",
                hue="status",
                data= movies_df, 
                height=8, aspect=2,
            showmeans=True,
                kind="box")
plt.show()

We observed the following pattern :

  • Comparing the rating dispersion,
    • it's immediately apparent (if not particularly surprising) that release movies which have ru ( Russia ) as original_language are rate higher than all the others.
    • Rumored movies are rate higher when they are in en ( English ) original_language
    • In production movies are not many in our dataset but the result is than the are higher rate with fi ( finnish or finland ) as original_language
  • No movies is for adult
